longBusinessSummary: Sphinx Resources Ltd. engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties in Canada. It primarily explores for zinc, copper, nickel, lead, palladium, platinum, gold, and silver deposits. The company holds 100% interests in the Calumet-Sud project with 21 claims covering 12.14 square kilometers located in Pontiac regional county municipality of southwestern Quebec; and the Green Palladium project with 74 claims covering 41 square kilometers. It also holds 100% interests in the Tessouat project with 22 claims comprising 13.16 square kilometers; the Tessouat-Sud project with 37 claims covering 22.21 square kilometers; and the Obwondiag project with 26 claims covering 15.65 square kilometers in southwestern Quebec. In addition, the company holds 100% interests in the Soufflot project, including 35 mining claims covering an area of 19.95 square kilometers; and Patrie project with 34 mining claims covering an area of 19.90 square kilometers located in the Temiscamingue gold belt. Further, it has an option to acquire a 100% interest in the Calumet-Nord project in the Proterozoic volcanic belt of l'Ãle-du-Grand-Calumet. The company was formerly known as Donner Metals Ltd. and changed its name to Sphinx Resources Ltd. in October 2014. Sphinx Resources Ltd. was incorporated in 2005 and is headquartered in Montreal, Canada.
